    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing free_positioning_information_resp() function causing memory leaks\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP positioning functionality was missing the required `free_positioning_information_resp()` function to properly clean up dynamically allocated memory in positioning response messages. This caused memory leaks when positioning procedures were used.\n\nThis fix adds the missing implementation file and function following the established patterns in the codebase.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c`: New file implementing positioning response handling functions\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.h`: New header declaring positioning response functions  \n- `openair2/COMMON/f1ap_messages_types.h`: Added `f1ap_positioning_information_response_t` structure\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/CMakeLists.txt`: Added new source file to build\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_lib_includes.h`: Added required ASN.1 includes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_lib_extern.h`: Added header include\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running gNB with positioning capabilities enabled, memory usage steadily increases during positioning procedures. Valgrind reports show unfreed memory blocks corresponding to SRS configuration and SFN timing fields in positioning response messages.\n\nThe missing function caused a linker error when other components tried to call `free_positioning_information_resp()`, indicating the function was expected to exist but was not implemented.\n"
}